23 Nov 2013 23:09








Is there a way to spread the word on this SCP without sounding like a overexcited fanboy?
附加记录：    

Write a tale about it, discuss it with the people in the IRC chatroom, draw some art with it as a subject, write a poem, mention that it's one of your favorites when asked. If you really like an SCP and feel like you're bursting with uncontrollable zeal over it, it's a better idea to put that energy into making a work of your own honoring it, than telling everyone else OMG IT'S AWESOME (because there's no guarantee that others will feel the same way about it). This SCP has been around for some time.

That said, I'm rather fond of it as well, seeing as it was pretty much the deciding reason that led me to join the site.

Also, there are a few other interesting butterfly SCPs out there that are pretty recent, including Avernus Vine. Happy reading!







